default version: runs ddfw with wrand pickmethod, new linear weight transfer rule (if clause_weight [source] > BASE_WEIGHT, returns BASE_WEIGHT), and CSPT=0.1. 
this version has two parameters (settable from the command line) for the linear rule: 
           (i) currpmille (range is (0, 1,000) ) and basepmille (range is (0, 10,000))
           (ii) currpmille: default value is 75, divided by 1,000 in the solver 
                basepmille: default value is 750, divided by 1,000 in the solver 
       command: ./yalsat --ddfwonly --innerrestartoff $CNF

NFM-best version: 
       command: ./yalsat --wtrule 3 --ddfwonly --innerrestartoff $CNF 
       will run the NFM-best version

Original DDFW version:
       command: ./yalsat --ddfwonly --innerrestartoff --wtrule 1 --basepmille 250 --greedy --clsselectp 1 $CNF
         will run the orignal ddfw version
